.TH ZVEC_NEW 3 2022-01-29 "ZC" "Linux Programmer's Manual"
.SH NAME
zvec_new \- create instance of opaque type
.IR zvec_t .
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <zvec.h>
.P
.BI "zvec_t* zvec_new(int32_t " cap ", uint32_t " soe ");
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR zvec_new()
function allocates
.I cap
*
.I soe
bytes for the internal void pointer when
.I cap
is no less than 0.
To use the default capacity just input 0.
.P
.I cap
is the initial capacity for the vector.
.P
.I soe
is the size of the element.
.P
This function uses
.BR malloc()
to allocate related memory blocks.
.SH RETURN VALUE
The
.BR zvec_new()
function return a pointer to the instance.
On error, it returns
.BR NULL .
.SH ERROR
.B malloc()
Out of memory.
.P
.I cap
is negative.
.SH ATTRIBUTES
For an explanation of the terms used in this section, see
.BR attributes (7).
.TS
allbox;
lb lb lb
l l l.
Interface	Attribute	Value
T{
.BR zvec_new ()
T}	Thread safety	MT-Safe
.TE
.SH SEE ALSO
.B malloc(3)
the allocation method.
.P
.B zvec_free(3)
free the resources referenced by the instance.
.P
.B zvec_slice(3)
create sub-vector from existing one.
